The paper deals with the problem of measuring the similarity of polygonal curves, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus of the paper is on developing a robust variant of the Frechet distance, which is a well-known measure of similarity between curves. This involves dealing with outliers, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper presents an algorithm for approximating the solution to the problem, which involves analyzing the complexity of the algorithm, making it relevant to the field of computational complexity (cs.CC).
